16/03/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- President Georgi Parvanov on Tuesday (15 March) officially called for the withdrawal of Bulgarian peacekeeping troops from Iraq by the end of this year.
In a statement broadcast on national media, Parvanov criticised the defence ministry and the army command over the recent death of a Bulgarian soldier killed by friendly fire in Iraq.
The president said poor co-ordination was to blame.
In other news Tuesday, Interior Ministry Chief Secretary Boyko Borissov denied the possibility of a radical Islamic network in the country.
He was responding to recent allegations in the Spanish press over last year's deadly Madrid train bombings.
(Trud, 24 Chasa, Sega - 16/03/05;
Mediapool, bTV - 15/03/05)
